  1. NEWS

  1. Spring Hydrant Flushing Begins April 15th

    Spring fire hydrant flushing will take place between 8 a.m. and 3:30 p.m., April 15th through May 3rd. Read more...

  2. Community Easter Egg Hunt To Be Held At Hanners Park on April 20th

    Hop into Canal Winchester on Saturday, April 20th at 10:00 a.m. (rain or shine) for the Canal Winchester Community Easter Egg Hunt, to be held this year at Hanners Park (458 Groveport Rd.) Read more...

  3. CW to Host Backyard Conservation Workshop on April 20th

    Attention local gardeners! A free backyard conservation workshop is scheduled to be held on April 20, 2019 from 1:00 p.m. to 2:30 p.m. at the Frances Steube Community Center (22 S. Trine St.) Read more...

  4. Canal Winchester Arbor Day Celebration April 26

    The city of Canal Winchester and Canal Winchester Local Schools will come together Friday, April 26th at approximately 2:15 p.m. to celebrate Arbor Day Read more...

  1. CW Prescription Drug Take-Back April 27th

    The City of Canal Winchester and Diley Ridge Medical Center, in cooperation with the Fairfield County Sheriff’s Office and the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA), will host a National Prescription Drug Take-Back event on April 27, 2019 Read more...

  2. 20th Annual Tree Giveaway May 4

    City of Canal Winchester residents will have the opportunity to pick up a free tree at the city’s 20th annual tree giveaway at Stradley Park, located at 36 S. High St. in historic downtown Canal Winchester, on May 4th from 9 a.m. to 11 a.m. Read more...

  3. Canal Winchester Named 2018 Tree City USA Community

    Canal Winchester was recently named a 2018 Tree City USA Community by the Arbor Day Foundation. The designation honors the city’s commitment to effective urban forest management. Read more...

  4. Elected Officials to Serve Dinner at Kris Sims Memorial Relay For Life Fundraiser May 15

    Get acquainted with Canal Winchester’s elected officials once again as they wait tables to earn tips for Relay for Life. On Wednesday, May 15, Mayor Mike Ebert and City Council members will serve dinner at the Frances Steube Community Center Read more...
